OL,3,CCriminals being freed from jail early
OL,4,Cto cut overcrowding
OL,6,FAnother inmate who had been released
OL,7,Fearly was recalled to custody before
OL,8,Fthe watchdog's inspection had ended.
OL,9,FAccording to the findings, he had a
OL,10,F"significant" drug problem and a
OL,11,Frecord of self-harm as well as
OL,12,Fexperiencing suicidal thoughts, but
OL,13,Fwas freed despite "appeals for the
OL,14,Fdecision to be reversed and staff
OL,15,Fhaving serious concerns for his and
OL,16,Fthe public's safety".
OL,18,FHe was homeless on release, according
OL,19,Fto the findings.
